        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('SpamAssassin'); ?>
        <p><strong>SpamAssassin</strong> is a computer program released under the Apache License 2.0 used for e-mail spam filtering based on content-matching rules. It is now part of the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Apache Foundation', 'C'); ?>.</p>
        <p>SpamAssassin uses a variety of spam detection techniques, that includes DNS based and fuzzy checksum based spam detection, Bayesian filtering, external programs, blacklists and online databases.</p>
        <p>The program can be integrated with the mail server to automatically filter all mail for a site. It can also be run by individual users on their own mailbox and integrates with several mail programs. SpamAssassin is highly configurable; if used as a system wide filter it can still be configured to support per-user preferences.</p>
        <p>SpamAssassin was awarded the Linux New Media Award 2006 as the "Best Linux-based Anti-spam Solution".</p>
